
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `brltty-lscmds` baraye list kardane hameye dastoorhaye `BrlAPI` ke dastras hastand estefade mishavad. `BrlAPI` yek interface baraye rabete ba braille display-ha ast. Ba estefade az in dastoor, mitavanid bebiniid che dastoorhayei baraye kontrol va modiriyat display braille mojood hast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    In dastoor gozinehaye ziadi nadarad, chon karash sade ast va list kardane dastoorha ast.
    🔹 Heech gozinehyeh khasii niaz nist --> Dastoor be soorat pishfarz hameye dastoorha ra neshan midahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ brltty-lscmds

    🔹 List kardane hameye dastoorhaye `BrlAPI`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ brltty-lscmds | grep keyboard

    🔹 List kardane hameye dastoorhaei ke dar an kalameh "keyboard" vojood darad.  In mesal baraye peyda kardane dastoorhaye marboote be keyboard display braille mofeed ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `brltty-lscmds` command is used to list all the available `BrlAPI` commands. `BrlAPI` is an interface for communicating with braille displays.  Using this command, you can see what commands are available for controlling and managing the braille display.

⚙️ **Options:**
    This command doesn't have many options because its purpose is simple: to list commands.
    🔹 No specific options are usually needed --> The command displays all commands by default.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ brltty-lscmds

    🔹 List all available `BrlAPI` commands.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ brltty-lscmds | grep keyboard

    🔹 List all commands that contain the word "keyboard". This example is useful for finding commands related to the braille display keyboard.
